{
  "text": "Culture. Gtv-a mice harboring gliomas were euthanized with CO 2 inhalation. The tumors were aseptically removed and enzymatically dissociated with trypsin-EDTA for 15 min at 37 \u2218 C. The digestion was stopped with DMEM containing 10% FBS. After trituration with a pipette, single cells were washed, plated, and cultured in DMEM containing 10% FBS, 100 mg/mL streptomycin, and 100 IU/mL penicillin at 37 \u2218 C in a humidified 5% CO 2 atmosphere. Normal mouse astrocytes were prepared from the primary mixed glial cell cultures of newborn ICR mice (SLC, Shizuoka, Japan), as described previously [CITATION_1] . Astrocytes were purified from the primary mixed glial cell cultures by three to four repetitions of trypsinization and replating. Cultures were maintained with DMEM supplemented with 10% FBS and 5 g/mL of bovine insulin. The astrocytes were grown to confluency, and the medium was exchanged every three days.",
